Title: ENABLING PRECISE INTERPRETATIONS OF SOFTWARE CHANGE DATA
Elements_risk_assessment: They don't look if the changes done were or weren't the real cause of the bug
UseOF-SZZ: Similar heuristics to map commits and ids
Summary:
computes a fine-grained edit script describing
    changes within a change set,identifies changes that we consider to be non-essential,and identifies subtasks within change sets, or groups of changes that are related to each other, but unrelated to other groups of changes within the same change set
Outcome: Proposed a catalog of non-essential changes and describe an automated technique for detecting such changes within version histories, between 3% and 26% of all modified code lines and between 2% and 16% of all method updates consisted entirely of non-essential modifications.
